{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876368223,"sessionID":"ses_2858574abffetaOmZRnfwqIZPi","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7ae2200017XP0aHa4VZzg5d","messageID":"msg_d7a7ad1f9001uQQ8tu235IbgsJ","sessionID":"ses_2858574abffetaOmZRnfwqIZPi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e90b1939aa69407aad66e5b1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing a comprehensive Makefile build target system for AgentCube, supporting Go source compilation, Docker image building, testing, linting, and development workflows.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-033\n10: - **Module**: `root`\n11: - **Language**: `Makefile`\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Scenario: Binary Build Targets\n17: \n18: ### AR-033-001: Build all binaries\n19: \n20: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root with Go source code\n21: - **WHEN** running `make build`\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL compile router, workload-manager, agentd, and picod binaries\n23: - **AND** SHALL place them in `bin/` directory\n24: - **AND** SHALL use CGO_ENABLED=0 for static linking\n25: - **AND** SHALL inject version via ldflags (-X main.version=$(BINARY_VERSION))\n26: \n27: ### AR-033-002: Build individual binary - router\n28: \n29: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n30: - **WHEN** running `make build-router`\n31: - **THEN** it SHALL compile only router binary\n32: - **AND** SHALL place it at `bin/router`\n33: \n34: ### AR-033-003: Build individual binary - workload-manager\n35: \n36: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n37: - **WHEN** running `make build-workload-manager`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL compile only workload-manager binary\n39: - **AND** SHALL place it at `bin/workload-manager`\n40: \n41: ### AR-033-004: Build individual binary - agentd\n42: \n43: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n44: - **WHEN** running `make build-agentd`\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL compile only agentd binary\n46: - **AND** SHALL place it at `bin/agentd`\n47: \n48: ### AR-033-005: Build individual binary - picod\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n51: - **WHEN** running `make build-picod`\n52: - **THEN** it SHALL compile only picod binary\n53: - **AND** SHALL place it at `bin/picod`\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Scenario: Cross-Compilation Targets\n58: \n59: ### AR-033-006: Build for Linux amd64\n60: \n61: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n62: - **WHEN** running `make build-linux-amd64`\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL compile all binaries for linux/amd64\n64: - **AND** SHALL place them in `bin/linux-amd64/` directory\n65: \n66: ### AR-033-007: Build for Linux arm64\n67: \n68: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n69: - **WHEN** running `make build-linux-arm64`\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL compile all binaries for linux/arm64\n71: - **AND** SHALL place them in `bin/linux-arm64/` directory\n72: \n73: ### AR-033-008: Build for Darwin amd64\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n76: - **WHEN** running `make build-darwin-amd64`\n77: - **THEN** it SHALL compile all binaries for darwin/amd64\n78: - **AND** SHALL place them in `bin/darwin-amd64/` directory\n79: \n80: ### AR-033-009: Build for Darwin arm64\n81: \n82: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n83: - **WHEN** running `make build-darwin-arm64`\n84: - **THEN** it SHALL compile all binaries for darwin/arm64\n85: - **AND** SHALL place them in `bin/darwin-arm64/` directory\n86: \n87: ### AR-033-010: Cross-build all platforms\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n90: - **WHEN** running `make cross-build`\n91: - **THEN** it SHALL execute all cross-compilation targets\n92: - **AND** SHALL produce binaries for linux-amd64, linux-arm64, darwin-amd64, darwin-arm64\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Scenario: Docker Build Integration\n97: \n98: ### AR-033-011: Docker build all images\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** Makefile with docker targets\n101: - **WHEN** running `make docker-build`\n102: - **THEN** it SHALL build router, workload-manager, and agentd images\n103: - **AND** SHALL tag each with :latest tag (unchanged from AR-032)\n104: \n105: ### AR-033-012: Docker build individual image - router\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n108: - **WHEN** running `make docker-build-router`\n109: - **THEN** it SHALL build only router image\n110: - **AND** SHALL tag as agentcube-router:latest\n111: \n112: ### AR-033-013: Docker build individual image - workload-manager\n113: \n114: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n115: - **WHEN** running `make docker-build-workload-manager`\n116: - **THEN** it SHALL build only workload-manager image\n117: - **AND** SHALL tag as agentcube-workload-manager:latest\n118: \n119: ### AR-033-014: Docker build individual image - agentd\n120: \n121: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n122: - **WHEN** running `make docker-build-agentd`\n123: - **THEN** it SHALL build only agentd image\n124: - **AND** SHALL tag as agentcube-agentd:latest\n125: \n126: ### AR-033-015: Docker push all images\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n129: - **WHEN** running `make docker-push`\n130: - **THEN** it SHALL push all 3 images to registry\n131: - **AND** SHALL push both versioned and latest tags\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ## Scenario: Testing Targets\n136: \n137: ### AR-033-016: Run all tests\n138: \n139: - **GIVEN** agentcube project with test files\n140: - **WHEN** running `make test`\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL execute unit tests\n142: - **AND** SHALL use `-short` flag to skip long-running tests\n143: - **AND** SHALL display test results verbosely\n144: \n145: ### AR-033-017: Run unit tests only\n146: \n147: - **GIVEN** agentcube project\n148: - **WHEN** running `make test-unit`\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL run only unit tests\n150: - **AND** SHALL skip integration tests\n151: - **AND** SHALL use `-v` for verbose output\n152: \n153: ### AR-033-018: Run tests with coverage\n154: \n155: - **GIVEN** agentcube project\n156: - **WHEN** running `make test-cover`\n157: - **THEN** it SHALL generate coverage profile (coverage.out)\n158: - **AND** SHALL generate HTML coverage report (coverage.html)\n159: - **AND** SHALL display coverage percentage\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Scenario: Code Quality Targets\n164: \n165: ### AR-033-019: Run linter\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** agentcube project with golangci-lint config\n168: - **WHEN** running `make lint`\n169: - **THEN** it SHALL execute golangci-lint on all packages\n170: - **AND** SHALL report any linting issues\n171: - **AND** SHALL exit with non-zero code if errors found\n172: \n173: ### AR-033-020: Run linter with auto-fix\n174: \n175: - **GIVEN** agentcube project\n176: - **WHEN** running `make lint-fix`\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL run golangci-lint with --fix flag\n178: - **AND** SHALL automatically fix fixable issues\n179: - **AND** SHALL report any unfixable issues\n180: \n181: ### AR-033-021: Format code\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** agentcube project\n184: - **WHEN** running `make fmt`\n185: - **THEN** it SHALL run gofmt on all Go files\n186: - **AND** SHALL run goimports to fix imports\n187: - **AND** SHALL write changes in-place (-w flag)\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ## Scenario: Development Workflow Targets\n192: \n193: ### AR-033-022: Start development environment\n194: \n195: - **GIVEN** agentcube project with docker-compose.dev.yml\n196: - **WHEN** running `make dev`\n197: - **THEN** it SHALL start development environment via docker-compose\n198: - **AND** SHALL run in detached mode\n199: \n200: ### AR-033-023: Start development with Docker\n201: \n202: - **GIVEN** agentcube project\n203: - **WHEN** running `make dev-docker`\n204: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d`\n205: - **AND** SHALL start all required services\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ## Scenario: Cleanup Targets\n210: \n211: ### AR-033-024: Clean build artifacts\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** agentcube project with built binaries\n214: - **WHEN** running `make clean`\n215: - **THEN** it SHALL remove `bin/` directory\n216: - **AND** SHALL remove coverage files (coverage.out, coverage.html)\n217: - **AND** SHALL remove any other build artifacts\n218: \n219: ### AR-033-025: Clean Docker images\n220: \n221: - **GIVEN** built Docker images\n222: - **WHEN** running `make docker-clean`\n223: - **THEN** it SHALL remove router, workload-manager, and agentd images\n224: - **AND** SHALL handle missing images gracefully (no error if not found)\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Scenario: Utility Targets\n229: \n230: ### AR-033-026: Display help\n231: \n232: - **GIVEN** Makefile with help target\n233: - **WHEN** running `make help`\n234: - **THEN** it SHALL display all available targets\n235: - **AND** SHALL show categorized help text\n236: - **AND** SHALL include descriptions for each target category\n237: \n238: ### AR-033-027: Display version\n239: \n240: - **GIVEN** Makefile with version target\n241: - **WHEN** running `make version`\n242: - **THEN** it SHALL display current build version\n243: - **AND** SHALL show BINARY_VERSION variable value\n244: \n245: ### AR-033-028: Check dependencies\n246: \n247: - **GIVEN** agentcube project\n248: - **WHEN** running `make deps`\n249: - **THEN** it SHALL verify Go is installed\n250: - **AND** SHALL verify Docker is installed\n251: - **AND** SHALL verify golangci-lint is installed (optional)\n252: - **AND** SHALL display helpful error message if any dependency is missing\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## Scenario: Variable Configuration\n257: \n258: ### AR-033-029: Docker registry configuration\n259: \n260: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n261: - **WHEN** running make with DOCKER_REGISTRY=<custom>\n262: - **THEN** it SHALL use custom registry prefix for image tags\n263: - **AND** default value SHALL be \"agentcube\"\n264: \n265: ### AR-033-030: Docker tag configuration\n266: \n267: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n268: - **WHEN** running make with DOCKER_TAG=<version>\n269: - **THEN** it SHALL use custom tag for images\n270: - **AND** default value SHALL be \"latest\"\n271: \n272: ### AR-033-031: Binary version configuration\n273: \n274: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n275: - **WHEN** running make with BINARY_VERSION=<version>\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL inject version into binary via ldflags\n277: - **AND** default value SHALL be \"dev\"\n278: \n279: ### AR-033-032: Go version configuration\n280: \n281: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n282: - **WHEN** running make with GO_VERSION=<version>\n283: - **THEN** it SHALL use specified Go version for Docker builds\n284: - **AND** default value SHALL be \"1.24\"\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## Scenario: Default Target\n289: \n290: ### AR-033-033: Default build target\n291: \n292: - **GIVEN** agentcube project root\n293: - **WHEN** running `make` without arguments\n294: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make build` by default\n295: - **AND** SHALL compile all binaries for current platform\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ## Scenario: Error Handling\n300: \n301: ### AR-033-034: Missing Go installation\n302: \n303: - **GIVEN** environment without Go installed\n304: - **WHEN** running any build target\n305: - **THEN** it SHALL display clear error message\n306: - **AND** SHALL indicate Go is required\n307: \n308: ### AR-033-035: Missing source code\n309: \n310: - **GIVEN** agentcube project missing cmd/ directories\n311: - **WHEN** running build target\n312: - **THEN** it SHALL fail with appropriate error from go build\n313: - **AND** SHALL not produce misleading error messages\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ## Scenario: Makefile Structure\n318: \n319: ### AR-033-036: Self-documenting makefile\n320: \n321: - **GIVEN** Makefile\n322: - **WHEN** examining makefile source\n323: - **THEN** it SHALL be organized in logical sections with comments\n324: - **AND** SHALL use .PHONY declarations for all non-file targets\n325: - **AND** SHALL define variables at the top for easy configuration\n326: \n327: ### AR-033-037: Platform-independent targets\n328: \n329: - **GIVEN** Makefile targets\n330: - **WHEN** running on Linux, macOS, or Windows\n331: - **THEN** targets SHALL execute correctly\n332: - **AND** SHALL avoid shell-specific commands\n333: \n334: ---\n335: \n336: ## References\n337: \n338: - AgentCube proposal: `changes/AR-033/proposal.md`\n339: - Existing Makefile: `Makefile`\n340: - AR-032: Dockerfile multi-stage builds (downstream consumer)\n341: - Go cross-compilation: https://go.dev/doc/install/source#environment\n342: - golangci-lint: https://golangci-lint.run/\n343: \n344: (End of file - total 311 lines)\n\n(End of file - total 344 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing a comprehensive Makefile build target system for AgentCube, supporting Go source compilation, Docker image building, testing, linting, and development workflows.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-033\n- **Module**: `root`\n- **Language**: `Makefile`\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Binary Build Targets\n\n### AR-033-001: Build all binaries\n\n- **GIVEN** agentcube project root with Go source code","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775876368199,"end":1775876368219}}}}
